  "doc_id": "6307",
  "text": "Multiple receptors are expressed on the surface of mast cells. The high affinity receptor for IgE (FceRI) is the most well known receptor in antigen (Ag)-mediated responses, whereas signaling induced by stem cell factor (SCF) and its receptor c-Kit also plays an important role in mast cell development and function [CITATION_1] . Binding of Ag recognized by bound IgE on mast cells results in dimerization of the receptor followed by phosphorylation of phospholipase Cγ1 (PLCγ1), which triggers release of calcium (Ca 2+ ) from internal stores. Ca 2+ is an important intracellular messenger in mast cells because it plays a major role not only in mast cell degranulation but also in eicosanoid generation [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
